1.title: The Magician
1.fullDesc: This person is a man of action. A creator with big potential. A tough, powerful persona. People look up to him. This person often runs his own business or has plans to start one. He knows a lot, tries to make his own way in life and hates being told what to do. Great communication skills, good at talking to people. However, if this person fails at developing his many talents, his personal grows will stagnate, unable to handle problems in life. It turns this person into egotist, lier. He uses his communication skills to harm and trick people. It becomes hard to maintain focus, will power, ability to withstand struggles for such people.

2.title: The High Priestess
2.fullDesc: Patient, emotional, sensitive person. He feels other people's mood, knows their need, senses their thoughts and inner desires. These persons will make a good psycologist, teacher, mentor. They look intellegent, well-manner, although a bit soft. Oftentimes they lack strength, endurance to overcome problems in life. They need to learn compasion without taking it to extreme, solving other people's problems instead of their own. They end up veing influenced by others too much. People drain their energy like vampires, because they let them. These persons need to learn how to break connections and burn bridges between them and negative people around.

3.title: The Empress
3.fullDesc: These people represent grows, life, motherhood. Most of all they value family and children in life. They become great parents. They love household chores, trying to keep everything clean and in place. Good economists, oftentimes have their own business. Strive for comfort and resources. And usually life presents them with everything: movey, happy marridge, social acceptance. All it takes for these people is to know the limit. Because otherwise these people become abusive egotist, showing their worse sides. They are extremely conservative and bossy, especially towards their children. Man often end up dependant on women, even when these women treat them like money resourse only. Women, on the other hand, have sexual or marriage problems. These people, in the worse case scenario, become obsessed with money and power.

4.title: Emperor
4.fullDesc: Confident, powerful, active person. He can easily lead other people. They're born with this. Often hot-headed, even aggressive. These people have practical, analytical mind. Value order and discipline. Success in life and job promotions are practicly guaranteed. This person knows his desires and strives to fulfill them. However, on the negative side, these people are often stubborn, bossy and mean. Women dominate their families, holding everything under strict control, especially their children. Men, on the other hand, seek for more power all the time, being it their work or home. They want to control everything, which is not that easy though. Instead it's better for them to learn how to handle emotions and be tolerant of others. Often terrible bores, stubborn as hell. Not willing to change, always ready to stand their ground, no matter what.

5.title: The Hierophant
5.fullDesc: These are very bright people, they have natural wisdom. Gentle, always calm and always ready to listen, to help with advice. These kids grow up quickly, from an early age they have very intelligent eyes. Often not interested in making friends with other kids the same age, they prefer spending time older ones, which is perfectly normal. But like other people, they have their own dark side: this person may become unbearably arrogant, hypocritical, talkative. He thinks he's always right, often uses his social status for his advantge. Much is given to them, but much required from them.

6.title: The Lovers
6.fullDesc: Very kind and peaceful souls. Calm and soft character. They love everyone, seek harmony and lead peaceful existence. But there is a small issue here. These people often face a hard choice in life. They can have two lovers at the same time, two jobs, two houses. It is very difficult for them to dwell on one thing, hence the constant doubts and uncertainties. They think too much before making any important decisions in their lives, which is why they miss good opportunities. In a negative aspect this person is in constant doubt, he is unlucky in love, because he does not dare to take the first step. These kinds of girls just sit and wait for the prince on a white horse to knock at their door.

7.title: The Chariot
7.fullDesc: This person is active and very mobile. He travels a lot, he is always interested in learning new things. He is bold, confident, loves risk. The life of such people, often, is not rich with serious problems. In a negative aspect, they are very arrogant and ignorant people, they even have a megalomania. They rush forward, not taking into account the danger on their way. in this case their life ends up filled with dangerous situations: accidents, injuries, operations. They need to be careful when traveling, follow the rules and limit the risks. Sometimes such people become very passive, they refused to be moved from a dead center. They may have criminal inclinations, possibly getting into a bad company.

8.title: Justice
8.fullDesc: This person is usually put in a difficult position in life. There are two possible situations. He could be given power and at the same time a constant temptation to break the rules. If a person honestly uses the power given to him - he comes out of the situation with dignity. And if not, then he himself is to blame for all his problems that inevitably start to haunt him. Punishment is usually severe. Often loss of freedom - and this is not necessarily an actual prison. On the other hand, this person can constantly come across people with power. And always these people will pressure him, treat unfairly. All this to force the person to be in the role of a victim. If he starts to take offense at life or people around, then again gets a punishment - deprivation of liberty, in all senses. Such a person needs to be wiser, give thanks for the opportunity to grow in stress and lead an honest life.

9.title: The Hermit
9.fullDesc: This person is silent, loves solitude and somtimes a bit difficult to talk to. He's not a big fan of noisy parties and big gatherings. He needs peace and quiet. He is full of wisdom, a true philosopher who tries to find answers to the most difficult questions of the universe. There is seriousness in his character, a reallistic and thorough approach to everything. These children don't receive enough love from their parents, they always feel unloved. They need more attention. In a negative aspect, this person can get sullenness, secrecy, fears, suicidal tendencies, fixation on their problems. It is necessary for such a person to develop an optimistic view of life, instead of shutting himself off from the outside world and being angry all the time.

10.title: The Wheel of Fortune
10.fullDesc: These people have a progressive mind, constantly learning and moving their life forward. Their fate is a bright kaleidoscope of events. This person can not sit still, he always needs to develop, travel, discover other cultures, improve spiritually. Sometimes they have a fairly hard and programmed fate. They seem to go with the flow, without trying to assert control over it. The wolrd is gray for these people. But, at the same time, they're not as simple as it might seem. These people pursue material things, they are lucky, they can really hit the lottery. However, life often gives these people hardships in the beginning and there's no escape for them. Maybe this is a rough childhood, a bad parenting. And then a stroke of luck - a happy marriage or a great job. Therefore, the greatest danger for these people is to get stuck in life, surrender to the will of fate and do nothing.

11.title: Strength
11.fullDesc: Oh, these people are fighters. They always stand their ground, fight for their rights. Brave and adventurous. Often take risks, even poor ones. They can't bear injustice, violence, falsehood. These are truly strong and active people. Usually quite emotional, hot-headed, hard to get in contact with. They often have problems when it comes to personal relationships. Why? Simply because they're bad tempered. Love is a drama for them, often jealous of their partner. They can't have peace in love, they need action, feelings, emotions. These people may become quite evil, ruthless and mean. They strive for power and wealth, they're aggresive, impulsive. Often unable to control their fury. They must build strong and reliable moral principles
